args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject (a legacy, outcome, or state) originates from or is produced by the object (events, actions, or processes).
args.justification: Both relations describe the historical legacy as explicitly stemming from or originating in specific types of collective action (public protest demonstrations and revolutions). This is a consistent source/origin predicate where the legacy is derived from those events.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject stands as a symbol, illustration, or reminder of the resilience or enduring power of the object.
args.justification: This relation captures that the legacy functions as a reminder or emblem of the enduring power of the human spirit, i.e., a symbolic/representational link rather than an origin or part-whole relation.
Both relations connect a historical legacy to the protests or revolutions from which it originates, i.e., they describe historical source/origin links between past events and their lasting impact.

This relation links a historical legacy to an abstract concept (human spirit) that it represents or exemplifies, forming a symbolic/representational family distinct from causal or compositional relations.
A legacy deriving from protests or revolutions expresses a source–outcome dependency, where past collective actions give rise to or cause the enduring legacy, fitting a causal/source grouping.

The legacy is said to highlight or symbolize the power of the human spirit, forming an associative representational link between a historical phenomenon and an abstract concept rather than a direct causal or compositional relation.
